# Navbar (site-wide)

The primary navigation is **one shared component** used on every page. Behaviour and markup must stay consistent everywhere.

## Source of truth

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `src/components/Navbar/` | `Navbar.jsx`, `MobileNavbarPill.jsx`, `NavLinksList.jsx`, `navLinks.js`, `useNavScrollReveal.js` |
| `src/components/NavLink.jsx` | Terminal-style link + typing interaction |
| `styles/components/navbar.css` | Desktop header + compact notch |
| `styles/components/mobile-nav-pill.css` | Mobile bottom pill only |
| `src/motion/presets.js` | Navbar morph + `mobileNavPillShellVariants`, `mobileNavPillMenuVariants` |

## Mounting

- Import only from `src/components/Navbar` (barrel).
- Render **once** in `SiteLayout` / `App.jsx` — never duplicate `<Navbar />` or reimplement header markup inside page sections.
- New routes/pages must not add their own header, logo row, or nav list.

## Locked behaviour

### Desktop / tablet (≥ 810px)

- Default: **centred compact frosted notch** (logo + links) — no full-width header.
- **Scroll hide**: notch hides while scrolling; after scroll pause (~180ms) it returns with blur + opacity dissolve (`useNavScrollReveal`).
- No hamburger on desktop.

### Mobile (< 810px)

- **No top header** — content starts at the viewport top.
- **Sticky bottom pill** (`MobileNavbarPill`): logo + hamburger in a frosted pill; tap bar (or toggle) expands the pill vertically with nav links; hamburger animates to close.
- **Scroll hide**: pill hides while scrolling; after scroll pause (~180ms) it returns with blur + opacity dissolve (`useMobilePillNavScroll`).
- Menu open: pill stays visible; `body.is-mobile-nav-open` locks scroll.
- Logo link stops propagation (home); bar tap toggles menu.

### All viewports

- Links defined only in `navLinks.js` (Projects, Playground, Notes, About).
- Escape closes mobile menu.
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` via existing motion presets.

## Do not

- Add per-page nav markup or alternate headers.
- Reintroduce a top mobile header or full-screen drawer.
- Enable desktop compact scroll morph on mobile.
- Change nav link set in page files — update `navLinks.js` only.
- Move navbar styles into page CSS (`homepage.css`, etc.) — keep chrome in `navbar.css` / `mobile-nav-pill.css`.

## Changing the navbar

Edit the Navbar module and matching CSS (`navbar.css` + `mobile-nav-pill.css`), then verify desktop scroll morph and mobile bottom pill on a long page.
